The paper discusses research portfolio analysis and topic prominence in the science system, which involves analyzing and prioritizing research options. The paper uses a model of science consisting of 91,726 topics, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories. The paper also discusses funding data and demand for research options, which could suggest the cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes the implications of the results for research planning and portfolio analysis, which could suggest the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
